The article is a statement by the President on the budget. The President calls for a balanced approach to the budget that promotes economic growth and job creation. He praises a bipartisan budget agreement that replaces some spending cuts known as "the sequester" and allows for investments in scientific research. The agreement also slightly reduces deficits over time and prevents another government shutdown. The President acknowledges that the agreement does not include everything he wanted, but emphasizes the importance of compromise. He urges Congress to pass a budget based on the agreement and highlights the need to make the economy work for every working American. The President calls for the extension of unemployment insurance and further efforts to expand growth and opportunity.